## What You Can Do

- **Full root access**: Install packages (`apt-get install -y ...`), modify system
  files, change configurations — no restrictions
- **Use the workspace**: Your project files are mounted at the workspace path above.
  All changes there persist to the host
- **Docker is available**: Build and run containers inside this sandbox
- **System tools are pre-installed**: git, curl, wget, python3, node, build-essential,
  and many more are ready to use
- **No confirmation needed**: This is a throwaway sandbox. Install packages, run
  builds, modify system settings without hesitation

## Best Practices

- Work within the workspace directory for persistent changes
- Use apt-get (not apt) for non-interactive package installation
- The container may be recreated between sessions — workspace files persist but
  system changes do not (unless persistent mode is enabled)
